The paper discusses deep learning methods for text generation, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning, particularly in the subfield of deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the practical applications of text generation models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the need for tuning to achieve good performance, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the possibility of using computer vision techniques for text generation, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
